summary: The worst part about this is whenever controversial crap happens between youtubers, internet personalities, celebrities etc. The...
body:
The worst part about this is whenever controversial crap happens between youtubers, internet personalities, celebrities etc. The part that’s easy but kinda sucks is to drop whatever material they have worked on, Projared has some interesting D&D videos that really touch up on the fun of starting your own campaign that now feel gross to watch.

I know the initial reaction is to get mad and go “who cares!?” but we all need to realize before they do whatever stupid garbage they pull, sometimes they have genuinely good content, projared was good at explaining what made retro games great and why they may or may not have been famous without occasionally shitting on them hard like many scream lord bad opinion videos tend to do.

So it always sucks to have to constantly drop a channel or two and their material cause it can help certain people through many different aspects of their lives. I’m not making light of the cheating at all.

But I mean aren’t we all at some point tired of having to cross another name off a list because of someone’s shitty actions?
